  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to evaluate the effects in terms of gas exchange, respiratory
      mechanics and comfort of breathing, of different assisted mechanical ventilation in ALI/ARDS
      patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      ALI/ARDS patients (during assisted ventilation) will be ventilated with different types of
      assisted ventilation (pressure support, pressure support plus sigh, BIPAP, variable
      ventilation) and gas exchange, comfort of breathing, respiratory mechanics and pattern of
      breathing will be measured.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
